
nsodbc -- ODBC Database Driver for NaviServer

This is an internal database driver that connects to ODBC databases for Win32
or Unix systems. Unix users need need to obtain the client drivers
from the database vendor or by using e.g. unixODBC (http://www.unixodbc.org/)


Installation:

After installing NaviServer and an ODBC driver, do

    make
    make install

in the source directory of the nsodbc. If NaviServer
is installed at an unusual place, provide

    NAVISERVER=/path-to-your-ns-installation

int the make commands above.


